description:
drh added on 2017-06-13 03:55:19:
When SQLite is compiled with SQLITE_ENABLE_STAT4, the following SQL causes
an assertion fault or segfault:
CREATE TABLE t1(x);
CREATE INDEX t1x ON t1(x);
INSERT INTO t1 VALUES(1),(2),(3);
ANALYZE;
SELECT * FROM t1 WHERE x = -(-1);
This bug appears to have been in the STAT4 code since its STAT4 was
first introduced in SQLite version 3.8.1 (2013-10-17).
